Texts.Chs: "...死亡侨民不会完全死去.许多人的结局都在大疗养院里, 在没有感觉的恐惧中慢慢枯萎. (这还没被公开过.)少数人的结局非常迅速: 转变成一种携带翅膀和知识的生物, 还有一种结局也许是升华, 成为一枚卵或者之类的东西. 这个值一千元以及邪恶和罪恶的诱惑..."
Texts.Eng: "...tomb-colonists do not exactly die. Many end in the Grand Sanatorium, withering slowly to insensate horror. (This is not publicised.) A few end in Emergence: transformation to a flimsy thing of wings and knowledge, an end in ecstacy, the delight of becoming an egg, of sorts. This is accounted a grand and vile and tempting sin..."

Texts.Chs: "概念就像砖头一样.他可以用来建造理性的法院.或者用它来砸窗户."
Texts.Eng: "A concept is a brick. It can be used to build a courthouse of reason. Or it can be thrown through the window."

Texts.Chs: "醒目的月蓝, 记忆和最明亮的珊瑚的蓝色."
Texts.Eng: "A wakes APOCYAN, the blue of memory and brightest coral."

Texts.Chs: "無法逃避的結局!" 一件发射鱼叉的强力武器.
Texts.Eng: "AN INESCAPABLE ENDING!" A potent weapon which permits Flensing attacks.

Texts.Chs: "给我带来海胆的核心,作为我的王."
Texts.Eng: "And bring me a Fluke-Core. For my Kin."

Texts.Chs: "在你的镜子之中, V 代表琉璃绿, 半梦半醒的颜色."
Texts.Eng: "Behind your mirror, V names VIRIC, the colour of shallow sleep."

Texts.Chs: "带给我一个警觉的雕像, 做我的新主教," 珊瑚之源说
Texts.Eng: "Bring me a Wakeful Idol, to be my new Bishop," the Principles said

Texts.Chs: "带给我一小块燧石, 作为我的卒," 珊瑚之源说
Texts.Eng: "Bring me a little flint, to be my new Paw," the Principles said

Texts.Chs: "给我带来怪物的牙齿, 作为我新的骑士.", 珊瑚之源说
Texts.Eng: "Bring me a monster's tooth, to be my new Night.", the Principles said

Texts.Chs: "心壳银, 作为我的新堡垒", 珊瑚之源说.
Texts.Eng: "Bring me heart-shelled silver, to be my new Root", the Principles said.

Texts.Chs: "星海黄色的C字母,记忆中太阳的颜色. 那些丰饶的,发出臭气的,真菌类的生物: 这些全都在星海黄的光辉中茁壮成长."
Texts.Eng: "C lights COSMOGONE, the colour of remembered suns. The fecund, the foetid, the fungal: these flourish in the glow of cosmogone."

Texts.Chs: "卡米努斯试验场: 靠后点站." 一件野蛮而令人恐惧的武器.
Texts.Eng: "Caminus Yards: Stand Well Back." A weapon of savage and alarming power.

Texts.Chs: "卡米努斯试验场: 我们一直爱着你." 这件强力的武器可以轻松撕开海兽的防护.
Texts.Eng: "Caminus Yards: We Have Always Loved You." A powerful weapon that permits Flensing attacks.

Texts.Chs: "不要再做這件事了." 卡特洛尔 & 哈瑟萨奇公司的新型号.
Texts.Eng: "DON'T DO IT AGAIN." One of C&H's newer models.

Texts.Chs: "畏惧她的利刃!" 李德彼特&斯坦罗德公司最可靠的一款,不用提太多. 允许你进行鱼叉攻击.
Texts.Eng: "Fear her touch!" One of L&S' more reliable pieces, which isn't saying much. Permits Flensing attacks.

Texts.Chs: "G代表着消逝的刚特褐灰, 是所有其他颜色被吞噬后所剩下的遗骸. 刚特褐灰可以在无尽的阴影中找到."
Texts.Eng: "G is lost in GANT, which remains when all other colours are eaten. Gant can be found where shadows are myriad."

Texts.Chs: "这里记录了一些穿越[xxxxx] 的细节,在[xxxxxx]的陪伴执行, 在 [xxxxxx]上...." [用这个提高你的交流值.未来的船长可以一直使用它除非你将它卖掉.]
Texts.Eng: "Herein are recorded certain details of a Voyage through [xxxxx] in the company of [xxxxxx], on [xxxxxx]...." [Use this to increase your Pages. Unless you sell it, future captains will have access to it.]

Texts.Chs: "我是自己命运的主人: 我是自己灵魂的船长." [你现在处于无情模式, 除了游戏基础的自动保存之外没有其他的储存槽位.如果你切换到仁慈模式你将失去这枚印章.]
Texts.Eng: "I am the master of my fate: I am the captain of my soul." [You are in Unforgiving mode, with no save slots besides the basic autosave. You will lose this token if you switch from Unforgiving to Merciful mode.]

Texts.Chs: "我必须把这个秘密藏在指尖王到不了的地方. 我希望在那之后他们不会继续打扰我. 所以我把它放在了寒霜城. 不是寒霜城的正中心. 我没疯. 但是,恩,它离寒霜城的正中心很近." [找到北方的寒霜城, 在倒数第二间密室找到机械师的秘密.]
Texts.Eng: "I had to hide the Secret somewhere the Fingerkings couldn't go. I hoped they'd leave me alone then. So I put it in Frostfound. Not the very heart of Frostfound. I'm not insane. But, um, quite close to the heart." [Find Frostfound, in the north, and retrieve the Mechanic's secret from the penultimate chamber.]

Texts.Chs: "I代表靛紫.没人记得为什么.靛紫为家中被遗忘的角落染色."
Texts.Eng: "I is for IRRIGO. No one remembers why. Irrigo colours the forgotten corners of home."

Texts.Chs: "我在制造引擎的时候需要帮助.它需要是活着的, 比如那石猪, 还有我, 呃, 很擅长金工." [从智慧监狱营救或者赎出来他, 智慧监狱位于汗国附近的莲花海中.他能帮助机械师完成工程.]
Texts.Eng: "I'll need help to build the engine. It'll need to be alive, like the Pigs, and I'm, er, better at metal." [Rescue or ransom him from Wisdom, in the Sea of Lilies near the Khanate to help the Tireless Mechanic complete his project.]

Texts.Chs: "這是個怪獸,你難道不這麼認為嗎?" 一件强力的鱼雷发射器.
Texts.Eng: "IT'S A MONSTER. ARE YOU?" A powerful weapon that relies on Torpedo attacks.

Texts.Chs:
"就像一道横梁跨越海泽,
横跨所有黄金年代!" [一件对寻找敌人非常有用的设备.]
Texts.Eng:
"Like a lane of beams athwart the sea,
Thro' all the circle of the golden year!" [An effective device for seeking enemies.]

Texts.Chs: "哦,是的, 今晚那个淹死的人在哼唱, 一首水中的歌就像鱼骨一样."
Texts.Eng: "Oh yes, the Drowned Man is humming tonight, a song in the water like the bones of fish."

Texts.Chs: "凡人啊,記住你將終有一死"
Texts.Eng: "Omnia mors perimit et nulli miseretur"

Texts.Chs: "P字母用黯蓝书写, 最深的海中的颜色. [有人在页边潦草的写道: 在大門之後是一片更無光的海]"
Texts.Eng: "P drowns in PELIGIN, the colour of the deepest zee. [Someone has scrawled in the margin: BEYOND THE GATE THERE IS A SEA MORE SUNLESS]"

Texts.Chs: "波阿狄西亞: 更強馬力,更低價格." 李德彼特&斯坦罗德公司能提供的最好产品,尽管通常情况下他们会偷工减料.
Texts.Eng: "THE BOADICEA: MORE POWER, LESS SUBTLETY." The best Leadbeater & Stainrod can supply, although as usual they've skimped on materials.

Texts.Chs: "用这个这就对了." 一个足够对付小型海兽和菜鸟海盗的武器.
Texts.Eng: "THIS WAY UP." A weapon which may serve against small monsters or feeble pirates.

Texts.Chs: "文登湾有这样一个小地方..."
Texts.Eng: "There's this little place in Venderbight..."

Texts.Chs: "这些就是驱动着巴扎的力量." 涡轮机运转着,发出巨量的热量.
Texts.Eng: "These are the forces that drive the Bazaar." The Impeller runs very, very hot.

Texts.Chs: "V 代表着黯紫罗兰,这血液的颜色要从尖端流出. 黯紫罗兰色的墨水用来签署最令人绝望的条约..."
Texts.Eng: "V marks VIOLANT when blood is shed in a spired place. Violant ink is employed for the most desperate treaties..."

Texts.Chs: "我們將密切關注." 这件武器的威力令人赞叹.
Texts.Eng: "WE SHALL COMPEL ATTENTION." A weapon of respectable power.

Texts.Chs: "把綠色的死水攪個天翻地覆!" 允许进行鱼雷攻击.
Texts.Eng: "WINNOW THE SLUMBERING GREEN!" Permits Torpedo attacks.

Texts.Chs: "我们需要曾经活着过的怪物材料. 因为我们没法拿到巴扎的心 (不,我们真的做不到), 我们会需要从黎明机器那里拿来的一些东西. 抱歉."[带来一个黎明元素, 一桶蓝宝石, 还有四十单位的阴暗黑骨, 带着机械师的秘密和令人不安的贤者,去噬王者的城堡.]
Texts.Eng: "We need once-living monster-material. And since we can't get the heart of the Bazaar (no, we really can't), we'll need something from the Dawn Machine. Sorry."[Take one Element of Dawn, one Casket of Sapphires, and forty units of Stygian Ivory, along with the Mechanic's Secret and the Unsettling Sage, to Kingeater's Castle.]

Texts.Chs: "你需要一些人去查看里面." [法布尔鼠助手对于气动老鼠传输机来说必不可少.]
Texts.Eng: "You wants someone to take a look inside that." [In combat, Rattus Faber Assistants can be deployed for quicker repairs. It's dangerous work. Don't expect them back.]

Texts.Chs: '蛀船虫' 鱼雷发射器轻便而致命.不要小瞧它们.
Texts.Eng: 'Seaworm' torpedoes are small but lethal. Don't underestimate them.

Texts.Chs:
'怪物猎人能找到并筛选出那些现实中的恐怖生物.她已经屠灭了深渊中发出光的生物, 在对海泽盛宴的回忆中吃掉了它的血肉, 用它的尸骨做成了武器.她曾经是个人类.' 
但是这个怪物猎人已经为辉煌的结局做好了准备. 黑色逐日者正在等待着.
Texts.Eng:
'The Monster-Hunter winnows the lesser terrors from the true. She has slain That Which Makes Light in the Deeps, eaten its flesh in remembrance of certain Feasts of the Zee, and fashioned her weapon from its remains. She was human, once.' 
But this Monster-Hunter is ready for a glorious ending. Icarus in Black awaits.

一本为孩子写的书. 每一页上都是一种地表无法找到但是却存在于地下的颜色.

[你每找到一种不可能的颜色都可以返回到监护官这里. 书页给了你一些线索, 但是你需要在远方的港口找到它们.]
Texts.Eng:
A book for children. One page is devoted to each of the colours of the Neath, which are not found on the Surface.

[Return to the Curator with each of the seven impossible colours in hand. The book's pages give you clues, but you'll need to seek far ports.]

Texts.Chs: 一箱煽动性的文件.仅仅是揭示出他们中有的人正在秘密对抗法律 .
Texts.Eng: A box of incendiary documents. Simply being aware of some of them is against laws too secret to have been written.

Texts.Chs: 满满一箱神秘的物品. 打开它!
Texts.Eng: A boxful of mystery. Open it!

Texts.Chs: 一枚猫眼琥珀的胸针,还有一个警告.
Texts.Eng: A brooch of amber cat's eyes, and a warning.

Texts.Chs: 一桶非常小,但是有着剃刀般牙齿的蛇状鱼.
Texts.Eng: A bucket of tiny but razor-toothed serpentlings.

Texts.Chs: 双木匠, 纺织工, 工程师的手,还有老鼠的所有技能.
Texts.Eng: A carpenter, weaver, engineer's hand and rat of all work.

Texts.Chs: 山洞里住满了流亡者.
Texts.Eng: A caveful of exiles.

Texts.Chs: 内置了镜子矩阵的匣子: 一个不可思议的设备,它被用来捕获阳光.
Texts.Eng: A chest with an embedded matrix of mirrors: an unlikely device for capturing sunlight.

Texts.Chs: 最终一个孩子会解出它...
Texts.Eng: A child could solve this. Eventually...

Texts.Chs: 雪孩子生于渴求之地平线.
Texts.Eng: A child of snow was born at the Avid Horizon.

Texts.Chs: 如果不包装怎么能叫雪茄.
Texts.Eng: A cigar is nothing without its wrapper.

Texts.Chs: 建立在巨兽背上一座一直在进行修补的城市. 和平的代价如此之深.
Texts.Eng: A city in constant repair, set upon the back of a great beast. The price of peace is profound.

Texts.Chs: 一箱特别的人类灵魂. 它永远也不会知道皇家海关的印章长什么样子. 因此, 它不能在市场中出售,你最好别在带着这些的时候被人抓到.
Texts.Eng: A crate of exceptional human souls. It has never known the tender touch of the Imperial Customs stamp. Consequently, it cannot be sold on the open market, and you'd better not be caught with it.

Texts.Chs: 一箱正在哀求的灵魂. 它上面没有盖海关的印章 - 这是走私货!
Texts.Eng: A crate of pleading souls. This one does not bear a customs stamp - it is contraband!

Texts.Chs: 诅咒降临到你身上: 无名的告别之神的诅咒.
Texts.Eng: A curse lies on you: the curse of the nameless god of farewells.

Texts.Chs: 诅咒降临到你身上: 高处与愤怒的无名神的诅咒.
Texts.Eng: A curse lies on you: the curse of the nameless god of high places and anger.

Texts.Chs: 一份关于达哈城中实际情况的报告.
Texts.Eng: A description of how things stand at Dahut.
A detailed report on a place of interest. The Admiralty would value it.

Texts.Chs: 一只威严的琥珀色大猫, 因为其对马鲛鱼的爱好而闻名. 但是水手对待她总是带有一种夸张的尊敬. 他们见过她在镜子中的样子...
Texts.Eng: A dignified tortoiseshell-tabby, notable mainly for her fondness for mackerel. But the zailors treat her with exaggerated respect. They've seen what she looks like in a mirror...

Texts.Chs: 一个建有酒馆和蜜馆的放荡走私者巢穴.
Texts.Eng: A dissolute smugglers' haven of alehouses and honey-dens.

Texts.Chs: 一块坠落的钟乳石: 一个塞满了战利品的僧院.
Texts.Eng: A fallen stalactite: a monastery filled with plunder.

Texts.Chs: 无政府主义者最可怕的对手.
Texts.Eng: A fierce old enemy of anarchists.

Texts.Chs: 一个果实,一个珠宝,还是一滴眼泪? 让植物学家来鉴定它吧.它尝起来有点像松果.
Texts.Eng: A fruit, a jewel, a tear? Leave that distinction to the botanists. It tastes a little like pine-nuts.

Texts.Chs: 一个雕刻着南方的印记的神龛,闪闪发光.
Texts.Eng: A glittering altar carved with the Signs of the South.

Texts.Chs: 海底的一张巨口, 不法之徒与水中生物的巢穴.
Texts.Eng: A great mouth in the zee-floor, home to a lawless, aquatic culture.

Texts.Chs: 每一桶里都有一百个梦.
Texts.Eng: A hundred dreams in every barrel.

Texts.Chs: 某种荣誉.
Texts.Eng: A kind of glory.

Texts.Chs: 一些关于如何扮演这些角色的知识. [有时候, 无知即是自由. 学到更多会造成更复杂的效应.]
Texts.Eng: A knowledge of roles and how they are to be played. [Sometimes, ignorance is freedom. Learning more will have complex effects.]

Texts.Chs: 来自一位几乎已死的人的信, 给旮旯的同志的道歉.
Texts.Eng: A letter from the Almost Dead Man, apologizing to a comrade in Nook.

Texts.Chs: 来自一位几乎已死的人的信, 向隐逸之地的一位爱人告别.
Texts.Eng: A letter from the Almost Dead Man, bidding farewell to a lover in Hideaway.

Texts.Chs: 来自一位几乎已死的人的信, 向安忒的某人宣读其永恒的爱.
Texts.Eng: A letter from the Almost Dead Man, professing his undying love to one in Anthe.

Texts.Chs: 一个有着宏伟顶冠的鹦鹉,只会说那些它认为足够优秀的挽诗. 它的内心一定十分悲伤.
Texts.Eng: A majestically crested bird which speaks only in competent elegiac poetry. It is of a melancholy disposition.

Texts.Chs: 一个问题很多的人正在你的船上.
Texts.Eng: A man with many questions is on your vessel.

Texts.Chs: 一个坐落在种玫人码头的人头攒动的市场, 专门面向收集者和古怪的人营业.
Texts.Eng: A market for collectors and eccentrics throngs on Roser's Wharf.

Texts.Chs: 背了一身债的忧郁老流浪汉. 带他回家. [当你带他回伦敦时,请确认你身上有6000回声的现金.]
Texts.Eng: A melancholy old rogue with a difficult debt. Take him home. [Be sure you have at least six thousand Echoes in cash when you do.]

Texts.Chs: 来自船墟的旋律
Texts.Eng: A melody from Wrack

Texts.Chs: 一件通过死亡传递的信件. [这会安全的放在你的住所里.]
Texts.Eng: A message transmitted through the medium of death. [This is stored safely in your Lodgings.]

Texts.Chs: 上百万支点燃的蜡烛. 圣会的聚集地.
Texts.Eng: A million candles glow. A congregation gathers.

Texts.Chs: 一件古怪的心金属武器.
Texts.Eng: A monstrous weapon of monstrous heartmetal.

Texts.Chs: 共鸣与力量的名字,被抛弃在高塔之中.现在它是你的了.
Texts.Eng: A name of force and resonance, abandoned in a high tower by the one who bore it. Now it's yours.

Texts.Chs: 国家一定要强大. 如果这达到0, 皮格莫特岛上会发生不好的事情.
Texts.Eng: A nation must be strong. If this reaches 0, bad things will happen on Pigmote Isle.

Texts.Chs: 一定要建立一个国家. 如果这达到0, 皮格莫特岛上会发生不好的事情.
Texts.Eng: A nation must build. If this reaches 0, bad things will happen on Pigmote Isle.

Texts.Chs: 国家需要希望. 如果这达到0, 皮格莫特岛上会发生不好的事情.
Texts.Eng: A nation needs hope. If this reaches 0, bad things will happen on Pigmote Isle.

Texts.Chs: 一份经过公正的拷贝静静地躺在 贝斯波恩 & 福林皮尔斯法律咨询中心的保险库里.另外一份,则由大巴扎保管. [这将会确认你的下一名船长能接管你的住所,还有你存在那里的所有遗产.]
Texts.Eng: A notarised copy rests securely in the vaults of Baseborn & Fowlingpiece. Another, in the vaults of the Bazaar itself. [This will ensure your next character inherits your Lodgings, along with any Heirlooms you have stored there.]

Texts.Chs: 你的书房里挂着一幅画, 是一个熟铁打造的浮标, 永无尽头地漂浮着, 光线刺穿了海泽的黑暗.你几乎能听到那钟声. [你之前的船长越过了世界的最东方.]
Texts.Eng: A painting hangs in your study, of a wrought-iron buoy, endlessly afloat, light piercing in the Neath's dark. You can almost hear the bell. [A captain of your lineage sailed east out of the world.]

Texts.Chs: 你的书房里挂着一幅画, 看起来像是一座不可能存在的山上缠绕着的迷雾. [你之前的船长越过了世界的最东方.]
Texts.Eng: A painting hangs in your study, of mist on the face of impossible mountains. [A captain of your lineage sailed east out of the world.]

Texts.Chs: 你的书房里挂着一幅画. 两名旅者在眺望着, 永远保持着这个姿势,就像他们目的地的光已经很近了. [你之前的船长越过了世界的最东方.]
Texts.Eng: A painting hangs in your study. Two travellers watch, forever, as the lights of their destination come closer. [A captain of your lineage sailed east out of the world.]

Texts.Chs: 未透露的过往
Texts.Eng: A past yet to be revealed

Texts.Chs: 浮现出的画.
Texts.Eng: A picture emerges.

Texts.Chs: 从巴扎上切下的一小块东西, 从合法的角度看, 这是属于你的.
Texts.Eng: A piece cut from the Bazaar, legally yours.

Texts.Chs: 手工制作愉悦的地方, 所有的东西都有价可循.
Texts.Eng: A place of handmade delights, all available for a price.

Texts.Chs: 一种笨重但是货仓很大的船.
Texts.Eng: A ponderous, capacious vessel.

Texts.Chs: 一座监狱岛. 或者瘤节先知的食品柜.
Texts.Eng: A prison island. Or the knot-oracles' larder.

Texts.Chs: 为骨雕馆而生的沉默溺亡者, 要将生命献给研究.
Texts.Eng: A quiet drownie borne for Scrimshander, to dedicate his life to research.

Texts.Chs: A renegade Clay Woman roams the zee, pillaging the ships of weaker captains.
Texts.Eng: A renegade Clay Woman roams the zee, pillaging the ships of weaker captains.

Texts.Chs: 为可汗的荣耀准备的报告
Texts.Eng: A report for Khan's Glory

Texts.Chs: 一份关于爱古处Fortas Kettle中正在进行的事情的报告.
Texts.Eng: A report of doings in the Fortas Kettle at Aigul.

Texts.Chs: 一份关于那盛开的港口中诸多事务的报告.
Texts.Eng: A report of the doings in the flourishing port.

Texts.Chs: 引擎困住了一头怒吼的巨兽.
Texts.Eng: A roaring beast of an engine.

Texts.Chs: 一个从好战的豚鼠维亚家来的很有学者风度的生物,那里的贵族先知先觉地偷到了一艘蒸汽船,逃出了伦敦评论家即将锁上的笼子.  这很显然.
Texts.Eng: A scholarly creature from a warlike nation of aristocratic guinea-pigs whose progenitors stole a steamer to escape the locked hutches of a London essayist.  Apparently.

Texts.Chs: 知识的一个碎片. [发现怪物和地点来获得碎片.足够数量的碎片可以合成秘密.]
Texts.Eng: A scrap of lore. [Discover monsters and locations to gain Fragments. Gain enough Fragments, and they'll combine into a Secret.]

Texts.Chs: 对那些跟屁虫很有用.
Texts.Eng: A severe disincentive to pursuit.

Texts.Chs: 一个阴影中的人给了你一个提议.
Texts.Eng: A shadowy figure has made you an offer.

Texts.Chs: 一个用玻璃和钢铁制造的复杂机器,闪着光. 在它的核心,一只蛇王怒吼着. 也许是魔术师在哀求着.
Texts.Eng: A shimmering complexus of steel and glass. In its heart, a serpent-king rages. Or so the Magician claims.

Texts.Chs: 猫岛海盗王对你信任的象征.
Texts.Eng: A sign of the trust of the Pirate-King of the Isle of Cats.

Texts.Chs: 一个看起来很阴险的小雕像... 但是它的眼神却带着某种恳求.
Texts.Eng: A sinister little squatting image... but its eyes are pleading.

Texts.Chs: 一块从天而降伤痕累累的陨铁, 有一辆独轮车那么大.它的两侧有发光的符文.
Texts.Eng: A sky-scarred hunk of meteoric iron, the size of a wheel-barrow. Burning glyphs mark its flanks.

Texts.Chs: 一大块从天而降的陨铁, 一辆手推车的大小. 在它的侧面闪着符文的火花.一个星星的种子在它里面. 它在看着你.你确定你知道你要拿这东西来做什么吗?
Texts.Eng: A sky-scarred hunk of meteoric iron, the size of a wheel-barrow. Burning glyphs mark its flanks. A star-spore lives in it. It's watching you. Are you sure you know what you're doing with this thing?

Texts.Chs: 一个微笑,一个眼神, 一个蝴蝶纹身. 对武器和引擎有着热情与专业知识.
Texts.Eng: A smile, a wink, a butterfly tattoo. An intense and detailed knowledge of weaponry and engines.

Texts.Chs: 一份对于当地事物不甚全面的描述.
Texts.Eng: A somewhat less than frank and full description of affairs.

Texts.Chs: 关于孤立和归属的歌, 同样歌唱了伟大之物和人性.
Texts.Eng: A song of isolation and belonging, of greatness and humility.

Texts.Chs: 关于暗流和泥沙的歌.
Texts.Eng: A song of undertows and silt.

Texts.Chs: 来自深处关于崇拜与爱慕的歌.
Texts.Eng: A song of worship and adoration from the depths.

Texts.Chs: 一个覆叶的继承人切下的部分.
Texts.Eng: A souvenir of one of the Cladery Heir's amputations.

Texts.Chs: 一堆笔记本, 上面是用珍贵的墨水写的密密麻麻的东西.
Texts.Eng: A stack of notebooks, closely written in treasure-ink.

Texts.Chs: 尾巴上的毒刺.
Texts.Eng: A sting in your tail.

Texts.Chs:
研究空地中间那棵不可能生长在地下的树, 关于一名船长撕毁画着大蛇的画像. 船长的船员在旁边冷静地观看着. 其中一个人口中分叉的舌头清晰可见. 绘画上被涂满了琉璃绿 - 半梦半醒的颜色, 这种颜色在地面无法看到.
你就是画中的船长; 你也是作画的那个人.
Texts.Eng:
A study of a clearing amid trees that do not grow in the Neath, of a zee-captain smashing the image of a painted serpent. The zee-captain's crew look on calmly. A forked tongue is visible in one's open mouth. The painting is tinted everywhere with viric - the greenish colour of shallow sleep, which cannot be seen on the surface of the world.
You are the zee-captain in the painting; you are also the painter.

Texts.Chs: 里面溢出了一些愤怒的光.有些时候它会发出咯咯声.最好不要打开它.
Texts.Eng: A sullen viric glow leaks from within. Sometimes it rattles. Best not open it.

Texts.Chs: 一个会思考的生物制作了它, 或者是大海冲刷出来的; 或者二者皆有.
Texts.Eng: A thinking creature made this, or the sea made this; or both.

Texts.Chs: 在汗国进行交易的许可证.
Texts.Eng: A token permitting you to trade in the Khanate.

Texts.Chs: 实用主义考古学家的工具.
Texts.Eng: A tool for pragmatic archeologists.

Texts.Chs: 胜利? 悔恨? 无论如何, 这都会留在你心中.
Texts.Eng: A triumph? A regret? Either way, it lingers in your mind.

Texts.Chs: 外交官,商人和富裕的间谍喜欢使用的型号.
Texts.Eng: A vessel for diplomats, merchants and wealthy spies.

Texts.Chs: 一团发出嘶嘶声的蒸汽困扰着你
Texts.Eng: A watchful hissing vapour haunts you

Texts.Chs: 一份爱情小说被安忒最好的意识修订.
Texts.Eng: A work of romantic literature that has been revised by the best Anthean minds.

Texts.Chs: 一个海怪镇纸, 用阴暗黑骨雕得很漂亮. [你之前的船长被证明是海怪之子]
Texts.Eng: A zee-monster paperweight, beautifully carved from Stygian ivory. [A previous captain in your lineage proved to be the child of a zee-monster]

Texts.Chs: 所有的都很丰裕,所有的都很充实.
Texts.Eng: All foison, all abundance.

Texts.Chs: 所有的东西尚未真正失去.
Texts.Eng: All is not quite lost.

Texts.Chs: 我们所有人都需要吃东西.
Texts.Eng: All of us must eat.

Texts.Chs: 所有心的历险都在这里, 用散文,诗歌或者绘画. 有些也许更适合私人享用. [附注:在伦敦, 所有的爱情故事都要缴税.即使是虚构的爱情故事也一样.]
Texts.Eng: All the adventures of the heart are here, in prose, poetry or pictorial form. Some may be more suitable for private consumption. [Note: in London, customs duty is paid on love stories. Even illustrated love stories.]

Texts.Chs: 所有的地狱之火, 还有所有的天堂之馨.
Texts.Eng: All the fire of Hell, and all the aroma of Heaven.

Texts.Chs: 麻衣人是旮旯的居民吗? 他和震动有什么关系?

Texts.Chs: 这是...一个灵魂? 它十分苍白而明亮. 他们说,像这样的灵魂是一个奇怪神明的孢子.
Texts.Eng: Is this... a soul? It's pale and bright. Souls like this, they say, are the spores of strange gods.

Texts.Chs: 你的颅骨足够锐利吗?
Texts.Eng: Is your skeleton as keen as it could be?

Texts.Chs: 你的舌头是一块软钻石吗? 你的言语闪光吗? 你的言语锐利吗?
Texts.Eng: Is your tongue a supple diamond? Does your speech glitter and stab?

Texts.Chs: It awaits the phrase that will open it.
Texts.Eng: It awaits the phrase that will open it.

Texts.Chs: 它闪着月蓝色的光. 为了争夺这样一块蓝色闪晶,人们不惜发动战争. [你能找到这东西的用处: 也许令人惊恐的学者会购买这东西.]
Texts.Eng: It blazes with apocyanic radiance. Wars have been fought for less. [You may find a use for this: or the Alarming Scholar will certainly purchase it.]

Texts.Chs: 回味起来有点苦.
Texts.Eng: It can leave a bitter aftertaste.

Texts.Chs: 它发着柔光. 足够照亮你进入旮旯的路程.
Texts.Eng: It glows softly. Enough to light your way in Nook.

Texts.Chs: 它确实有锋利的爪子; 上面有吓人的钩状物; 但是现在它看起来并不想用它的爪子.
Texts.Eng: It has claws; it has a fierce double beak; but just now it seems disinclined to use them.

Texts.Chs: 它被精心地上了一遍漆, 它的眼睛闪着光, 看起来让人很有食欲.
Texts.Eng: It is beautifully enamelled. Its eyes glisten like digestive fluid.

Texts.Chs: 这很难得.
Texts.Eng: It is hard-earned.

Texts.Chs: 融化是它的本质.
Texts.Eng: It is in its nature to melt.

Texts.Chs: 它不会轻易表现出来的.
Texts.Eng: It is not given lightly.

Texts.Chs: 它在早晨被种下, 中午就长得很高了,下午出现花蕾,在晚间枯萎. 外国人必须在它倒下之前回到船上.
Texts.Eng: It is planted in the morning, grows tall by lunch, buds in the afternoon, and withers in the evening. Foreigners must return to their ships before it falls.

Texts.Chs: 这是能冲上岸的最可怕也最罕见的东西.
Texts.Eng: It is rare something so awful washes up on shore.

Texts.Chs: 据说有七个人试图将不朽普及.
Texts.Eng: It is said that seven once tried to democratise death.

Texts.Chs: 据说如果你需要打破达哈的幻境, 那么你需要吃掉它. 但是请小心.
Texts.Eng: It is said you may eat it if you ever need to break an illusion at Dahut. But be cautious.

Texts.Chs: 很幸运, 它正在睡.
Texts.Eng: It is, fortunately, sleeping.

Texts.Chs: 这能制造最大规模的爆炸. 不是你所想要的优雅兵器, 但是它能制造最强烈的爆炸. [威严型是只能向前射击的火炮: 其他的是鱼雷和鱼叉类武器.]
Texts.Eng: It makes the most tremendous bang. Not what you'd call an elegant weapon, but it does make the most tremendous bang. [The Majesty is the only front-mounted pure cannon: others are torpedoes or flensing weapons.]

Texts.Chs: 它有可能是某种鱼,但是最好不要离太近看.
Texts.Eng: It might be some sort of fish, but best not to look too closely.

Texts.Chs: 它只能持续这么长时间...
Texts.Eng: It only lasts so long...

Texts.Chs: 这看起来并没有坏处; 最坏会发生什么?
Texts.Eng: It seems innocuous enough; what's the worst that could happen?

Texts.Chs: 更疼了. [一旦你的伤势达到3, 你就会死. 在住处休息会治愈你, 有时海中的事件也会治愈.]
Texts.Eng: It stings rather. [If you ever have three Wounds, you're dead. They will heal when you rest in your Lodgings, and from time to time at zee.]

Texts.Chs: It thrums. It wanders. It has a delightful stink. [This ship is available players who backed Sunless Sea at the Navigator Tier or higher. 它将在日后DLC中开放.]
Texts.Eng: It thrums. It wanders. It has a delightful stink. [This ship is available players who backed Sunless Sea at the Navigator Tier or higher. It will become available as DLC at a later date.]

Texts.Chs: 这曾经是个好地方. 好吧,并没有那么好.
Texts.Eng: It was a nice place once. Well, no it wasn't.

Texts.Chs: 一名不善言辞的将军把那里命名为玛瑙港. 之后她发现那里到处都是蓝宝石. 想想她对此有多尴尬.
Texts.Eng: It was the Laconic General who named the Carnelian Coast. Then she discovered it was full of sapphires. Imagine her embarrassment.

Texts.Chs: 这也是第一版. [你之前的船长完成了一部关于海泽的史诗.]
Texts.Eng: It's a first edition, too. [A captain of your lineage wrote the definitive work of maritime literature.]

Texts.Chs: 这可能是件好事?
Texts.Eng: It's a good thing. Probably?

Texts.Chs: 它不是个有吸引力的东西. 也许你不会把它留在壁炉架上.
Texts.Eng: It's not an attractive object. Perhaps you won't keep it on your mantelpiece.

Texts.Chs: 它非常危险, 但是既然它如此美丽,又有谁在乎呢?
Texts.Eng: It's very dangerous, but who cares when it's so pretty?

Texts.Chs: 它在很远的地方;但是也许它在注意着你.
Texts.Eng: It's very far away; but perhaps it's watching you.

Texts.Chs: 它在看着你; 如果它真的存在.
Texts.Eng: It's watching you; if it even exists.

Texts.Chs: 它的兄弟姐妹抛弃了它. 珍珠色的光从它的头冠上发出. 珊瑚之源曾经碰过它, 而且是用不那么温柔的方法. 但是它烹饪鱼肉和盐的手法简直就是个奇迹...
Texts.Eng: Its brothers and sisters have abandoned it. Pearly light drips from its mantle-crest. The Principles have touched it, and not gently. But it can work miracles with salt and fish-flesh...

Texts.Chs: 它的眼中闪着警惕的光. 它的忧郁已经消散: 现在你似乎有了某种预感.
Texts.Eng: Its eyes glitter with awareness. Its melancholy has dissipated: now you sense anticipation.

Texts.Chs: 它的坏脾气让它失去了船员的宠幸,但是这也让它成为了一只很有效率的捕鼠者 .
Texts.Eng: Its perpetual ill temper does not endear it to the crew, but it does make it an effective ratter.

Texts.Chs: 它的双翅承载了几千年的记忆.其中只有一小部分是美好的记忆.
Texts.Eng: Its wings carry a thousand years of memories. Few of those memories are good.

On the very edge of London's influence, curious matters are conducted.

Texts.Chs: 她有要去骨雕馆的理由. 她也有个理由要去刚特极点. 她几乎已经下定了决心.
Texts.Eng: She had a reason for coming to Scrimshander. And she has a reason for travelling to the Gant Pole. She's almost sure of it.

Texts.Chs: 她有她的答案. 该回到何方了.
Texts.Eng: She has her answer. It is time to return to Whither.

Texts.Chs: 她对见血表示无所谓. 但是她非常不喜欢衣服上的血污.
Texts.Eng: She has no difficulties with blood. But she very much dislikes bloodstains.

Texts.Chs: 她在伦敦外的远方狩猎, 既针对其他的海盗, 也针对那些旅行太远的旅者.
Texts.Eng: She hunts far from London, picking off both other pirates and travellers who zailed too far.

Texts.Chs: 她知道火焰的用法. 但是她并不适应海泽. 把她带到伦敦, 去黄铜大使馆.
Texts.Eng: She knows the uses of fire. But she's not cut out for the zee. Take her to London, and the Brass Embassy.

Texts.Chs: 她从没真正笑过.
Texts.Eng: She never quite smiles.

Texts.Chs: 她更喜欢人们称她为花园女士. 或者蔷薇就好.
Texts.Eng: She prefers Lady of the Gardens. Or just Zaira.

Texts.Chs: 她在玛瑙港等你.
Texts.Eng: She waits in Port Carnelian.

Texts.Chs: 她在黑暗中等待着.
Texts.Eng: She waits in the dark.

Texts.Chs: 她是猎户塔楼的三姐妹中最年轻的. 现在她已无家可归. 她不会向你展示她的脸, 更不会说发生了什么,但是她已经准备好用她的知识治愈你的船员...
Texts.Eng: She was the youngest sister of the Hunter's Keep three. Now her home is gone. She will not show her face, nor speak of what occurred, but she is prepared to use her education to help heal your crew...

Texts.Chs: 她看起来比以前阴郁了一些.
Texts.Eng: She's a little more sombre than she used to be.

Texts.Chs: 她正在瓦解, 但是至少她离终点不远了.
Texts.Eng: She's falling apart, but at least she doesn't have far too go.

Texts.Chs: 她曾给将军们看病,也曾和军队一起行军. 千万别惹她.
Texts.Eng: She's marched with armies and cured generals. Don't annoy her.

Texts.Chs: 一些活蹦乱跳的奇怪生物. 它被安全的囚禁着,只是可能.

Texts.Chs: 有时候可以在伦敦雇用他, 但他更经常出现在遥远北方的某个港口.

Sometimes available for hire in London.

Texts.Chs: 说出正确的密语, 齿轮就会排成一列为盒子解锁. 但是正确的密语是什么? [令人惊恐的学者也许会知道些什么.]
Texts.Eng: Speak the right phrase, and the tumblers will align and unlock it. But what is the right phrase? [The Alarming Scholar may have some ideas.]

Texts.Chs: 不确定性调谐: 相比于技术,更多的只是理论. [调谐器不影响你隐匿的能力.]

Texts.Chs: 悬浮在一片看起来像是海盐碎块的东西中. 手掌帝国那位高贵的总管主张这会很有用.
Texts.Eng: Suspended in what feels like a chip of zee-salt. The Exquisite Seneschal of the Empire of Hands claims it will be useful.

Texts.Chs: 城在哭喊.
Texts.Eng: THE CITY CRIES OUT.

Texts.Chs: 地虹
Texts.Eng: THE NEATHBOW

Texts.Chs: 在安忒获取港口报告并交给海军.
Texts.Eng: Take a port report at Anthe and then submit it at the Admiralty.

Texts.Chs: 把这带给手掌帝国换取奖励
Texts.Eng: Take it to the Empire of Hands for a reward

Texts.Chs: 花了太长时间, 他可能会带上你.
Texts.Eng: Take too much time and he may take you.

Texts.Chs: 带着光进入到黑暗的地带.
Texts.Eng: Taking light into the dark places.

Texts.Chs: 恐怖故事!!
Texts.Eng: Tale of Terror!!

Texts.Chs: 尝起来就像新鲜的空气和姜汁的结晶.它还有着一个奇怪的性质,如果你把它洒在炖肉里,它能够暂时麻痹声带.
Texts.Eng: Tastes like clean air and crystallised ginger. Also has the interesting property of paralysing the vocal chords if you sprinkle it in your stew.

Texts.Chs: 茶叶就是文明. 但是咖啡是革命. [在这达到 5之前, 你可以一直用咖啡豆提升你的价值.]
Texts.Eng: Tea is civilisation. But coffee is revolution. [Until this reaches 5, you can keep improving your Estate with coffee beans.]

Texts.Chs: 技术上来讲他们是乘客而不是货物. 但是你永远不知道他们是否会说些什么. [死亡聚居地会为这些乘客买单: 把他们在那里卖掉.]
Texts.Eng: Technically, passengers rather than goods. But you'd never know it to talk to them. [They'll pay their passage to the Tomb-Colonies: sell them there.]

Texts.Chs: 每一个仔细填满垫料的箱子里都装了十瓶. [这东西就算是合法使用也太过危险. 把它带到伦敦时要格外小心.]
Texts.Eng: Ten marked vials packed in a carefully padded casket. [This stuff is too dangerous even to be properly illegal. Be cautious in taking it to London.]

Texts.Chs: 伊利里亚是一款过时的型号, 但是它也能把你带到你想去的地方.
Texts.Eng: The 'Illyrian' is an outdated model, but it'll get you where you need to go.

Texts.Chs: 将军有个任务给你. 访问特定的港口来收取战略情报,然后回到将军这里.
Texts.Eng: The Admiralty has a task for you. Visit the named port to retrieve Strategic Intelligence, and return it to the Admiralty.

Texts.Chs: 诸多相关信息中, 海军尤其对海盗做的生意感兴趣.
Texts.Eng: The Admiralty, among others, is always interested in pirate business.

Texts.Chs: 几乎死去的人希望问心无愧地结束这复杂的生命.
Texts.Eng: The Almost Dead Man hopes to end a complicated life with a clear conscience.

Texts.Chs: 盲眼壮汉想要说些什么.
Texts.Eng: The Blind Bruiser attends to business on the dock.
The Boke of Sharpes

Texts.Chs: 大汉有个新任务.
Texts.Eng: The Bruiser has new assignments.

Texts.Chs: 那个炮手有冷静的一面; 尽管不是太冷静.
Texts.Eng: The Cannoneer  has a calmer side; although not much calmer.

Texts.Chs: 切洛内特的猎人们相信历史是英雄故事的结局. 一名明智的史学家从他们的行动中得到了启示并皈依了他们的英雄行为.
Texts.Eng: The Chelonate hunters believe history is the result of heroic words and deeds. A wise historian learns from their actions and embraces their heroism.

Texts.Chs: 切洛内特的大战士想要演一出关于伟大英雄的戏剧. 在档案馆中找到材料, 然后他们会给你一个英雄的奖励. 不是暗讽他们戏剧中的那些故事.
Texts.Eng: The Chelonate's champions want to put on a play about a great hero. Find them source material in the archives and they'll give you a hero's reward. But a proper one, not an ironically tragic one that they get in the stories.

Texts.Chs: 骨雕记录者的心已经很疲惫, 但是他的食物十分丰盛... 他几乎会用一切东西煲汤.
Texts.Eng: The Chronicler's heart is weary, but his meals are hearty... and he can make soup out of almost anything.

Texts.Chs: 一座记忆之城, 在此, 历史即战场.
Texts.Eng: The City of Memory, where history is a battleground.

Texts.Chs: 覆叶之心
Texts.Eng: The Cladery Heart

Texts.Chs: 覆叶的继承人可以做这个手术.
Texts.Eng: The Cladery Heir can do this surgery.

Texts.Chs: 覆叶的继承人从你身上摘下了什么.
Texts.Eng: The Cladery Heir removed something from you.

Texts.Chs: 冬日的猩红禽兽蛰伏在你的船舱之中.
Texts.Eng: The Crimson Beast of Winter lurks in your hold.

Texts.Chs: 阳光的残酷行为
Texts.Eng: The Cruelty of Sunlight

Texts.Chs: 手掌帝国为你安排了和钢铁共和国进行氢气交易的相关事项.
Texts.Eng: The Empire of Hands has charged you with arranging deliveries of hydrogen from the Iron Republic.

Texts.Chs: 手掌帝国将需要它去它要去的地方.
Texts.Eng: The Empire of Hands will need it to get where it's going.

Texts.Chs: 手掌帝国将来的旅途上会需要这些的.
Texts.Eng: The Empire of Hands will need them all where it's going.

Texts.Chs: 手掌帝国最神圣的岛屿, 无论任何阶层的猴子对这里都充满了尊敬.
Texts.Eng: The Empire of Hands' most sacred island, to whatever degree the monkeys are capable of such respect.

Texts.Chs: 灵魂的帝国需要灵魂来抬升它那些受过诅咒的居民.
Texts.Eng: The Empire of Souls needs them to uplift its unblessed civilians.

Texts.Chs: 平明王最珍视的财产. 顺带, 其中包含七人团之一布尔丹最后的那部分.
Texts.Eng: The Fair King's most treasured possession. Incidentally, it contains the last vestige of Bourdain, who was one of the Seven Against Nidah.

Texts.Eng: The Fathomking has given you what you need. Take it to your destination.

Texts.Chs: 深寻王想要你去见证一些最古老的存在的死亡, 并回来.
Texts.Eng: The Fathomking wishes you to witness the death of something that is the oldest of its kind, and return.

Texts.Eng: The Gods of the Zee: Stone's Curse

Texts.Chs: 海泽之神: 石头, 风暴和盐
Texts.Eng: The Gods of the Zee: Stone, Storm and Salt

Texts.Chs: 海泽之神: 风暴神的注意
Texts.Eng: The Gods of the Zee: Storm's Attention

Texts.Chs: 海泽之神: 风暴神的诅咒
Texts.Eng: The Gods of the Zee: Storm's Curse

Texts.Chs: 肠卜者从近死的海兽内脏中拉出了它们.
Texts.Eng: The Haruspex draws them from the viscera of the nearly dead.

Texts.Chs: 世纪之树的心
Texts.Eng: The Heart of the Tree of Ages

Texts.Chs: 麻衣人造了个钻头. 它正在慢慢钻入大嘴.
Texts.Eng: The Hempen Man has build a drill. It bores slowly into the Maw.

Texts.Chs: 威严的姐姐要求你调查他弟弟的悔恨.
Texts.Eng: The Imperious Sister has asked you to investigate the regrets of her Brother.

Texts.Chs: 幽暗储藏库被小心翼翼地保护着. 就像大多数在档案馆中的人一样, 任何逗留时间超过受欢迎程度的人都有可能惨遭不幸.
Texts.Eng: The Ivory Archives are jealously guarded. Like most of the figures in the archives, anyone overstaying their welcome is likely to meet a grisly end.

Texts.Chs: 汗国不信任其他任何国家, 但是尤其不信任伦敦.
Texts.Eng: The Khanate distrusts all foreign nations, but London in particular.

Texts.Chs: 汗国的势力正在增长.
Texts.Eng: The Khanate's power is growing.

Texts.Chs: 国王的爪牙依旧控制着猫岛.
Texts.Eng: The King's Claw keeps order on the Isle of Cats.

Texts.Chs: 紫丁香色的女士
Texts.Eng: The Lady in Lilac

Texts.Chs: 最后的治安官: 德莫岛
Texts.Eng: The Last Constable: Demeaux Island

Texts.Chs: 最后的治安官: 加德的哀悼
Texts.Eng: The Last Constable: Gaider's Mourn

Texts.Chs: 最后的治安官: 可汗之心
Texts.Eng: The Last Constable: Khan's Heart

Texts.Chs: 最后的治安官: 寻找中
Texts.Eng: The Last Constable: On The Trail

Texts.Chs: 最后的治安官: 文登湾
Texts.Eng: The Last Constable: Venderbight

Texts.Chs: 东方的印记
Texts.Eng: The Mark of the East

Texts.Chs: 机械师的秘密
Texts.Eng: The Mechanic's Secret

Texts.Chs: 无情的衣帽商
Texts.Eng: The Merciless Modiste

Texts.Chs: 无情衣帽商的心
Texts.Eng: The Merciless Modiste's Heart

Texts.Chs: 一定是猴子遗孤丢掉的.
Texts.Eng: The Monkey Foundling must have dropped it.

Texts.Chs: 地下世界最伟大的探险家, 至少她自己是这么认为的.把她和她的保镖带到手掌帝国.
Texts.Eng: The Neath's greatest explorer, in her own mind at least. Take her and her bodyguard to the Empire of Hands.

Texts.Chs: 海盗诗人留下的印记.
Texts.Eng: The Pirate-Poet has left her mark.

Texts.Chs: 神秘的邮政局长亲自签署的这封信. [你之前的船长在寄错的邮包中找到了骨头.]
Texts.Eng: The Postmaster Cryptic herself signed this letter. [A previous captain in your lineage found bones in a misaddressed package.]

Texts.Chs: 囚犯被囚禁在达哈.
Texts.Eng: The Prisoner is imprisoned at Dahut.

Texts.Chs: 谨慎的魔术师
Texts.Eng: The Prudent Magician

Texts.Chs: 囊块挖掘者已经把神经索交给了麻衣人.
Texts.Eng: The Pulp-Miners have been giving nerve-cord to the Hempen Man.

Texts.Chs: 税务员移除了其中可能引起争议的部分, 然后在书的封皮上盖上了海关的印章.
Texts.Eng: The Revenue Men have removed the most challenging elements, and applied a customs stamp to the title leaf.

Texts.Chs: 满足的魔术师
Texts.Eng: The Satisfied Magician

Texts.Chs: 伤痕累累的妹妹
Texts.Eng: The Scarred Sister

Texts.Chs: 北方的伤痕
Texts.Eng: The Scars of the North

Texts.Chs: 学者的笔记
Texts.Eng: The Scholar's Notes

Texts.Chs: 蛇纹机
Texts.Eng: The Serpentine

Texts.Chs: 想要研究系缆藻的药剂师.
Texts.Eng: The Severe Chemist wishes to study tether.

Texts.Chs: 银树: Pride
Texts.Eng: The Silver Tree: Pride

Texts.Chs: 银树: 传令官
Texts.Eng: The Silver Tree: The Herald

Texts.Chs: 南方的碰触
Texts.Eng: The Touch of the South

Texts.Chs: 进行长箱交易可能会让你认识更多的人.
Texts.Eng: The Trade in Long Boxes may lead you to meet new people.

Texts.Chs: 那些破坏者已经把这些破碎而伤心的石材从盐狮的两翼撬了下来.一名伦敦的联络员会交易这些.
Texts.Eng: The Unmakers have smashed these sad and rubbly remnants off the flanks of a Salt Lion. A contact in London will purchase them.

Texts.Chs: 未决的打捞者想要航向远方找到她.
Texts.Eng: The Unsettled Salvager is willing to zail far to find her.

Texts.Chs: 彬彬有礼的魔术师
Texts.Eng: The Urbane Magician

Texts.Chs: 西方的烙印
Texts.Eng: The Western Stigma

Texts.Chs: 社会人士和海员为他进行了募捐. [你之前的船长的父亲牺牲了自己来拯救他的船员.]
Texts.Eng: The Zociety of Zeafarers took up a collection to have this struck. [A previous captain in your lineage found that their father had sacrificed himself to save his crew.]

Texts.Chs: 海泽之歌
Texts.Eng: The Zong of the Zee

Texts.Chs: 看穿溺亡者幻术的能力.
Texts.Eng: The ability to see through the glamours of the Drownies.

Texts.Chs: 一名船员的梦, 在他的船长被黑女士带走之后剩下来的.
Texts.Eng: The account a certain zubmarine crew's dreams, after their captain was allegedly taken by Lady Black.

Texts.Chs: 一个无知的年代永远无法否定的可怕而大胆的猜测. [如果你出售了这个,你就会发现它难以取代.]
Texts.Eng: The awful daring of a moment's supposition which an age of ignorance can never deny. [If you sell this, you may not find it easy to replace.]

Texts.Chs: 皇家海军的脊梁, 当然是海军还有脊梁的时候.
Texts.Eng: The backbone of the Royal Navy, back when the Navy had a backbone.

Texts.Chs: 这些黑色的海怪骨头可以制作出令人惊讶的束胸衣.
Texts.Eng: The black bones of zee-monsters make for startling corsets.

Texts.Chs: 真菌虫悄悄潜入了加了三道锁的大门里.
Texts.Eng: The blemmigan has crept in through the triple-locked gate.

Texts.Chs: 真菌虫在死者之间会过得很好的.
Texts.Eng: The blemmigan will live well amongst the dead.

Texts.Chs: 这座明亮的瓦尔查斯城严格地限制访客的人数.
Texts.Eng: The brightly lit town of Varchas allows visitors in limited numbers.

Texts.Chs: 西部主镜的管理者兄弟; 对黑眼的男孩和酒没有抵抗力.
Texts.Eng: The brother of the Keeper of the Western Principal Mirror; has a weakness for wine and dark-eyed boys.

Texts.Chs: 时间正在流逝!
Texts.Eng: The clock is ticking!

Texts.Chs: 汤的颜色就像是雪地上的风干血迹. 汤的味道就像是蘑菇,辣椒和铁锈混在一起的味道. 至于配方,被严格保密.
Texts.Eng: The colour: old blood on snow. The taste: paprika, mushrooms, irony. The recipe: closely guarded.

Texts.Chs: 珊瑚正在变化...
Texts.Eng: The coral is changing...

Texts.Chs: 奇怪的手掌帝国无情的心脏
Texts.Eng: The cruel heart of the whimsical Empire of Hands

Texts.Chs: 珊瑚源的奇怪事务困扰着伦敦并激起了伦敦的兴趣.
Texts.Eng: The curious business of the Principles perplexes and intrigues London.

Texts.Chs: 深渊无法在你面前藏起秘密.
Texts.Eng: The deep cannot hide its secrets from you.

Texts.Chs: 你对达哈之美的沉迷深度.
Texts.Eng: The depth of your commitment to the beauty of Dahut.

Texts.Chs: 隐逸之地的居民们认识到了他们面临的状况吗?
Texts.Eng: The dwellers of Hideaway are well aware of the truth of their situation. Aren't they?

Texts.Chs: 隐逸之地的居民不相信外来者.
Texts.Eng: The dwellers of Hideaway don't trust those from outside.

Texts.Chs: 在旮旯停留造成的影响可以再爱古消去, 那里可以牺牲掉记忆.
Texts.Eng: The effects of prolonged stays in Nook can be reduced in Aigul, where memories are sacrificed.

Texts.Chs: 那些流亡者不说话,那些猴子则只是暴躁的发出吱吱声. 尽管如此,这里也有信息值得收集.
Texts.Eng: The exiles do not speak, and the monkeys merely chatter grumpily. Still, there is information to be gleaned here.

Texts.Chs: 对辽阔而黑暗的海泽的恐惧, 还有那些更深的东西. [用上岸的方式降低恐惧, 尤其是在伦敦. 如果当你回到伦敦时恐惧高于50, 你的恐惧值会下降到50.]
Texts.Eng: The fear of the wide black zee, and the things beyond. [Reduce this with Shore Leave, especially in London. When you return to London after time at zee, your Terror will always drop to 50.]

Texts.Chs: 格林菲尔德蘑菇园最棒的一批.
Texts.Eng: The finest output of the Greyfields shroom-yards.

Texts.Chs: 远古巨兽走向死亡的被遗忘之深渊.
Texts.Eng: The forgotten depths where the elder beasts of the zee go to die.

Texts.Chs: 这些碎片被骄傲地展示在饰板上. [你之前的船长在噬王者的城堡里找到了遗骨]
Texts.Eng: The fragments are proudly displayed on a lacquered plaque. [A previous captain in your lineage found bones at Kingeater's Castle]

Texts.Chs: 心是无心的猎人. [你和一名船官开始了一段谨慎的关系.]
Texts.Eng: The heart is a heedless hunter. [You are engaged in a discreet liaison with one of your Officers.]

Texts.Chs: 这是最强大的海怪:流浪之山或者世纪之树的心, 也许.
Texts.Eng: The heart of one of the great monsters: Mt Nomad or the Tree of Ages, perhaps.

Texts.Chs: 很正式的纪念照. 被雨水浸湿的名字很难读出来. [在你之前的那名船长找到并埋葬了他父亲的遗骨,或者遗骨的代替品.]
Texts.Eng: The image of an imposing memorial. The rain-blurred name is difficult to read. [A previous captain in your lineage found and buried their father's bones - or a substitute.]

Texts.Chs: 农西奥的居民对友谊很迟钝,而且抱有怀疑态度.
Texts.Eng: The inhabitants of Nuncio are slow to friendship, and suspicious.

Texts.Chs: 海泽中的岛屿一直在变化
Texts.Eng: The islands of the zee are always in motion

Texts.Chs: 最敏锐的头脑通常也是最脆弱的.
Texts.Eng: The keenest minds are often the most fragile.

Texts.Chs: 刀在你手中显得十分沉重.
Texts.Eng: The knife is heavy in your hand.

Texts.Chs: 最后的秘密?
Texts.Eng: The last secret?

Texts.Chs: 这个岛上最近的新闻是那些偷灵魂的猿类. 科学的讲, 是猴子.
Texts.Eng: The latest news from the island of soul-stealing apes. Technically, monkeys.

Texts.Chs: 光芒耀眼而炽热. 很少有人能忍受那里的强光.
Texts.Eng: The light dazzles and burns. Few can tolerate its strength.

Texts.Chs: 塔楼上的光消失了.
Texts.Eng: The lights are gone from the Keep.

Texts.Chs: 古大陆的光在你的血液中涌动.
Texts.Eng: The lights of the Elder Continent swim in your blood.

Texts.Chs: 失踪的旮旯的孩子们曾经住在这里.
Texts.Eng: The missing Nook children once lived here.

Texts.Chs: 你呼吸越多, 你对空气的记忆就越少.
Texts.Eng: The more of it you breathe, the less you remember air.

Texts.Chs: 欧洲和更远地方的国家, 正在为影响力进行竞争. 他们的密谋甚至到达了地下. [将军和外交官, 会比其他人对此更感兴趣.]
Texts.Eng: The nations of Europe, and beyond, compete for influence. Their plots reach even to the Neath. [The Admiral and the Diplomat, among others, will be interested to hear this.]

Texts.Chs: 这些淡黄色东西的本质不甚明朗, 不过它们不太可能是恶魔的遗骨这件事倒是很确定. 它们通常保存在密封的小罐子里,也许会被某些人用作弹药.
Texts.Eng: The nature of these yellowish morsels is unclear, except that they are unlikely to be composed of deceased devils. They are kept in sealed cannisters, possibly as ammunition.
The nuns endure.

Texts.Chs: 来自它甲壳质核心的最古老最致命的蜘蛛状生物. 最致命的,感谢上天它死了.
Texts.Eng: The oldest and deadliest arachnid from its chitinous core. Deadliest, and now thankfully dead.

Texts.Chs: 手掌帝国唯一的人类定居点
Texts.Eng: The only human settlement in the Empire of Hands

Texts.Chs: 这些湿地里的哲学家们的日常生活是辩论,争吵与祈祷.
Texts.Eng: The philosophers of the swamp debate, squabble and pray.

Texts.Chs: 里面的画像是一个小小的金发婴儿.
Texts.Eng: The picture of a small blonde baby is inside.

Texts.Chs: 加德的哀悼那边的海盗告诉了你许多关于那个粘土海匪的故事.
Texts.Eng: The pirates of Gaider's Mourn tell many tales of this clay corsair.

Texts.Chs: 无法容留你的地方, 压碎了你. 你身上依旧有伤势.
Texts.Eng: The place which is no-place held you, crushed you. You carry the wounds still.

Texts.Chs: 你得到的奖励在伦敦等着你. 回到你的住处领取.
Texts.Eng: The prizes you've taken await you in London. Claim them at your Lodgings.

Texts.Chs: 这个问题一定要问Fortas Kettle的大副.
Texts.Eng: The question one must ask the First Mate of the Fortas Kettle.

Texts.Chs: 巨大乌龟壳的遗留. 贪婪的猎人. 腐败中的血肉.
Texts.Eng: The remains of a vast turtle shell. Voracious hunters. Rotting flesh.

Texts.Chs: 照片上的人有一个共同点. 他们都在微笑. [你之前的那名船长找到并救出了他的父亲.]
Texts.Eng: The resemblance is obvious. Both are smiling. [A previous captain in your lineage found and rescued their father.]

Texts.Chs: 老鳗的尊重
Texts.Eng: The respect of the Conodont

Texts.Chs: 维瑟吉为你分配的角色.
Texts.Eng: The role assigned on the island of Visage.

Texts.Chs: 所有好事的根源. [和你的船官讨论秘密来提升技能. 你可以通过右键点击他们的头像来和他们交谈.]
Texts.Eng: The root of all good. [Discuss Secrets with your Officers to improve your skills. You can speak to your Officers by right-clicking their portraits.]

Texts.Chs: 你很难错过那个雕像.
Texts.Eng: The statue's hard to miss.

Texts.Chs: 旮旯中奇怪的事情使得其居民异常谨慎.
Texts.Eng: The strange goings on in Nook force its people to be unusually wary.

Texts.Chs: 这个治疗会在伊瑞暮发生.
Texts.Eng: The treatment will occur at Irem.

Texts.Chs: 这些石材的用途是个谜.你必须把它们送到哪里?
Texts.Eng: The uses of the stone are mysterious. Where must you take it?

Texts.Chs: 波浪在你头顶之上.
Texts.Eng: The waves are above you.

Texts.Chs: 通向地表的路, 工程学的奇迹. 将军对这里有适中的兴趣.
Texts.Eng: The way to the Surface, and a marvel of engineering. The Admiralty has a very modest interest.

Texts.Chs: 船墟的居民依赖于沉船. 他们是怎么发展的?
Texts.Eng: The wreckers rely on the ships they sink to survive. How are they faring?

Texts.Chs: 越过噬王者城堡的海域黑暗而宁静.
Texts.Eng: The zee beyond Kingeater's Castle is dark and empty.

Texts.Chs: 这座围墙中的光明之城中酝酿着黑暗的阴谋.
Texts.Eng: There are dark machinations in the walled city of light.

Texts.Chs: 海泽中存在着一些强大的力量.
Texts.Eng: There are powers.

Texts.Chs: 她的眼睛现在有着豹子的锐利目光.
Texts.Eng: There is a pantherine glint in her eye now.

Texts.Chs: 她的沉默中有一道轻微的裂痕.
Texts.Eng: There is a slight fissure in her reserve.

Texts.Chs: 这里还有许多等待发现的东西. 但是这已经满足需要了.
Texts.Eng: There is much still to discover here. But this will suffice for now.

Texts.Chs: 更深的深处有些东西.
Texts.Eng: There is something in the deeper depths.

Texts.Chs: 现在来看, 只是一个大蘑菇.
Texts.Eng: There's only one of it. For now.

Texts.Chs: 这个东西可以在伦敦的遗忘区找到. 魔术师会为你打开这个区域.
Texts.Eng: These can be found in the Forgotten Quarter of London, which the Genial Magician can open for you.

Texts.Chs: 这些既不生长在这个世界里也不生长在这个世界外.
Texts.Eng: These do not grow on or under the world.

Texts.Chs: 这些信件曾经无法递送,但是现在信封上有了新的地址.
Texts.Eng: These letters used to be dead, but they now have new addresses on them.

Texts.Chs: 这些曾经是诗人,谋杀犯或者牧师... 或者是船长. 这个箱子上印着海关的标识.
Texts.Eng: These were poets or murderers or priests... or zee-captains. This crate bears a customs mark.

Texts.Chs: 它们一直在看着. 你也是.
Texts.Eng: They are always watching. So are you.

Texts.Chs: 那城墙比女王的宫殿还高, 比无畏舰的长度还厚, 是黑色的玄武石建造的. 你要怎么摧毁它?
Texts.Eng: They are taller than the Empress' Palace, thicker than the length of a dreadnought, and built from black basalt. How are you to breach them?

Texts.Chs: 他们上了你的小艇. 带他们去牧羊人群岛.
Texts.Eng: They made it to your boat. Take them to the Shepherd Isles.

Texts.Chs: 他们在屋顶上制造了这些, 并且不会说为什么. [一件一次性物品,在战斗中对双方产生无法照亮的黑暗, 增加恐惧.]
Texts.Eng: They make these on the roof-tops, and won't say why. [A one-use item that will remove all Illumination from both sides in combat, and increase Terror.]

Texts.Chs: 据说幽暗储藏库中有些东西能追溯到历史的开端. 但是没人知道那到底是什么.
Texts.Eng: They say the Ivory Archives contains stories going back to the start of history. But they aren't very clear on when that was.

Texts.Chs: 这不会治愈敏锐的军医, 但是也许这能让她撑更长时间.
Texts.Eng: They won't cure the Brisk Campaigner, but perhaps they'll grant her a little more time.

Texts.Chs: 他们崇拜瓦尔查斯的太阳, 并且已经把黑暗从城市中流放出去.
Texts.Eng: They worship the sun in Varchas, and have banished darkness from the city.

Texts.Chs: 眼眶被厚厚的骨板覆盖, 就好像是要把眼眶隐藏或保护起来. 它们摸起来又光滑又冰冷. 靛紫的光从它颚骨的缝隙处溢出.
Texts.Eng: Thick plates of bone have developed over the orbits, as if to hide or protect them. They are smooth and cold to the touch. Irrigo light glimmers in the line of the jaw.

Texts.Chs: 这个粘土人用他的灰色巨手抓着捕光镜匣,他看起来有点困惑. 如果他知道应该期待什么,他会看起来比现在困惑得多. [这将能让不知疲倦的机械师睡上一觉.]
Texts.Eng: This Clay Man looks confused as it grasps the Mirrorcatch Box in its great grey hands. It would look a lot more confused if it knew what to expect. [This will allow the Tireless Mechanic to get a night's sleep.]

Texts.Chs: 这个能力可以在达哈或者其他什么地方获取.
Texts.Eng: This ability can be earned at Dahut or in a few other places.

Texts.Chs: 这几乎不能称得上是一本书. 几打纸片塞进另外两张纸片. 每张上面都印着一条对针对谋杀的有用建议, 还有, 一些血迹.
Texts.Eng: This barely qualifies as a book. Dozens of scraps of paper have been crammed into a scuffed folio. Each bears helpful advice on murder, and, often, a stain.

Texts.Chs: 这个属于博物馆!假定殖民帝国对税务支配权进行拨款是对不同文化间接触的合理反应.也许吧, 因为博物馆是个复杂而庞大的官僚机构.  [如果你订立了遗嘱,你可以把这个转化为一件继承物来留给你的继任者.]
Texts.Eng: This belongs in a museum! Assuming that colonial-imperial appropriation for the purpose of hegemonic taxonomisation is a suitable response to the problem of intercultural contact. Which it probably is, because museums are magnificent institutions.  [If you've made an Ironclad Will, you can convert a collection of these into an Heirloom for your successor.]

Texts.Eng: This dreamy, furtive fellow is travelling to the Principles of Coral.

Texts.Eng: This tramp steamer has served well, but for a long, long, long time.

Texts.Eng: Violant: the colour of necessary, but troublesome connections. According to other traditions, the colour of blood shed in a spired place. It's very hard to forget anything you've written in violant ink...

Texts.Eng: Vitality and intelligence. What would we do without them? Especially if we're spies, diplomats, or pirates.

Texts.Chs: 我們會工作.我們只會工作. [这三个粘土司炉会降低你需要的船员数量,但是也会降低船员容量, 轻微提升引擎功率.它们放在附属物槽位.当他们被卸下来时, 他们会耐心地站着,手牵着手,带着不可读的灰色眼神. 其中一个有时会说: "我喜歡它安靜的樣子."]
Texts.Eng: WE WILL WORK. WE WILL ONLY WORK. [This trio of Clay stokers will reduce crew requirements, but also crew capacity, and will slightly increase engine power. They are fitted to an Auxiliary slot. When they are not in use, they will stand, patiently, hands by their sides, flat grey eyes unreadable. One will say, sometimes: "I LIKE IT WHEN IT IS QUIET."]

Texts.Eng: You Fear Nothing More Than Death

Texts.Eng: You Fear Something More Than Death

Texts.Chs: 你让覆叶的继承人使邮差不再是邮差.
Texts.Eng: You allowed the Cladery Heir to make a postman no longer a postman.

Texts.Chs: 你已经很接近了.
Texts.Eng: You approach an exaltation.

Texts.Chs: 你正在帮助贪婪的神学家.
Texts.Eng: You are assisting an Avaricious Theologist.

Texts.Chs: 你发现了农西奥的事情是怎么回事.
Texts.Eng: You are discovering how things are at Nuncio.

Texts.Chs: 你参与了一件太过荒谬的事情,这件事情接近真正的非法.
Texts.Eng: You are engaged in an activity too monstrous even to be truly illegal.

Texts.Chs: 你正在探索这座道路曲折的迷宫.
Texts.Eng: You are exploring this maze of twisted passages.

Texts.Chs: 你离家很远.
Texts.Eng: You are far from home.

Texts.Chs: 你正在调查食烛者.
Texts.Eng: You are investigating Snuffers.

Texts.Chs: 你了解了些关于曾林的静谧小径的事情. [提升到7才能找到你正在找的东西.]
Texts.Eng: You are learning the Waswood's silent paths. [Increase this to 7 to find what you seek.]

Texts.Chs: 你已经不是之前的自己了.
Texts.Eng: You are not as you were before.

Texts.Chs: 你正在玩弄新羊岛
Texts.Eng: You are playing New Mutton Island

Texts.Chs: You are playing with the original Pigmote Isle
Texts.Eng: You are playing with the original Pigmote Isle

Texts.Chs: 你正在寻找可以打开海中捞上的密语锁箱的密语.
Texts.Eng: You are seeking the phrase that will open a whisper-locked sea-chest.

Texts.Chs: 你被看见了.
Texts.Eng: You are seen.

Texts.Chs: 你想要从莲花海中的监狱里救出一名囚犯...
Texts.Eng: You attempted to rescue a prisoner from the prison in the Sea of Lilies...

Texts.Chs: 你一度成为了某种古代之物的一部分.
Texts.Eng: You briefly became part of something ancient.

Texts.Chs: 至少你可以确认,  他们就在他们现在所说的地方.
Texts.Eng: You can confirm, at least, that they are where they are.

Texts.Chs: 在岛屿完全封闭之前你只能尽力救人.
Texts.Eng: You can only rescue so many before the island is fully locked down.

Texts.Chs: 你不能允许船墟人危害无辜. 尤其是那些会为你的警告付钱的无辜.
Texts.Eng: You cannot allow the Wreckers to claim innocents. Particularly innocents that may pay for their warning.

Texts.Chs: 你带上了一个诅咒: 家与治愈的无名神的诅咒.
Texts.Eng: You carry a curse: the curse of the nameless god of home and healing.

Texts.Chs: 你选择了伦敦的爱人.
Texts.Eng: You chose a sweetheart in Fallen London.

Texts.Chs: 你根本不关心这些神,无论是真实的还是虚构的. 你会走你自己的路. [这不会让你免遭海泽中神的诅咒.]
Texts.Eng: You don't care for gods, real or imagined. You'll make your own way. [This does not protect you from the curses of the zee-gods.]

Texts.Chs: 你踏入了圣地.
Texts.Eng: You entered a sacred place.

Texts.Chs: 你找到了一只画中的大蛇.
Texts.Eng: You found a painted serpent.

Texts.Chs: 你找到了一些有价值的东西! [每轮游戏只有一次, 有些好事会发生.]
Texts.Eng: You found something valuable! [Once per game, something pleasant will happen.]

Texts.Chs: You freed Iria - by killing the ironbird, but mercifully
Texts.Eng: You freed Iria - by killing the ironbird, but mercifully

Texts.Chs: You freed Iria - by unbinding the ironbird from winter...
Texts.Eng: You freed Iria - by unbinding the ironbird from winter...

Texts.Chs: You freed Iria - by utterly destroying the ironbird
Texts.Eng: You freed Iria - by utterly destroying the ironbird

Texts.Chs: 你给了一名邮差离开农西奥的机会.
Texts.Eng: You gave a postman an opportunity to leave Nuncio.

Texts.Chs: 你船上的某个地方藏了一只偷脸的污秽生物. 它宣称对这些受害者的遭遇负责.
Texts.Eng: You have a face-stealing abomination somewhere on your ship. It's claimed this many victims.

Texts.Chs: 你在海泽里有对手了.
Texts.Eng: You have a rival at zee.

Texts.Chs: 你和维也纳的咖啡屋有了互助的关系.
Texts.Eng: You have a useful relationship with a coffee-house in Vienna.

Texts.Chs: 你已拥有 潜艇DLC.
Texts.Eng: You have access to the Zubmariner DLC expansion.

Texts.Chs: 你要送一封重要的信. [在物品栏中查看信件来确认目的地位置.]
Texts.Eng: You have an important message to deliver. [Look at the letter in your inventory to see its destination.]

Texts.Chs: 你对什么东西困扰着他有个模糊的了解.
Texts.Eng: You have an inkling of what haunts him.

Texts.Chs: 你被要求带信去加德的哀悼.
Texts.Eng: You have been asked to deliver a message to Gaider's Mourn.

Texts.Chs: 你已经把命运和这些豚鼠连接在了一起.
Texts.Eng: You have cast your lot in with the Cavies.

Texts.Chs: 你已经把你的命运和这些老鼠连接在了一起.
Texts.Eng: You have cast your lot in with the rats.

Texts.Chs: 你在海中探索来寻找秘密和其他的财富.
Texts.Eng: You have combed the zee for stories and other treasures.

Texts.Chs: 你把这个倒霉的家伙关在了货仓底的笼子里. [囚犯靠剩饭维生一般情况下不消耗你的补给品. 通过使用这件物品释放你的囚犯, 或者出于某种目的把他们带回伦敦...]
Texts.Eng: You have confined this unfortunate to a cage in the hold. [Prisoners survive on scraps and do not usually require Supplies. Release your Prisoner by using this item, or take them back to London for other purposes...]

Texts.Chs: 你为海军部服务过，他们不会忘记的。
Texts.Eng: You have done service for the Admiralty, and they won't forget it.

Texts.Chs: 你帮了旮旯的人们一个大忙. 他们比其他冒着泡泡的大嘴更珍惜你的存在.
Texts.Eng: You have done the people of Nook great service. They begrudge your presence less than that of other bubble-mouths.

Texts.Chs: 你遭遇了救世主岩礁的大蜘蛛议会.
Texts.Eng: You have encountered the grand spider-council of Saviour's Rocks.

Texts.Chs: 你和一名船官开始了一段关系, 在海泽之上.
Texts.Eng: You have engaged in a liaison with one of your officers, out at zee.

Texts.Chs: 你已经探索了达哈.
Texts.Eng: You have explored Dahut.

Texts.Chs: 你已经探索了沉没的巴内特.
Texts.Eng: You have explored Low Barnet.

Texts.Chs: 你发现了手掌帝国的机遇
Texts.Eng: You have found adventure in the Empire of Hands

Texts.Chs: 你已经找到了蛾子和哀痛的隐秘巢穴.
Texts.Eng: You have found the secluded home of moths and mourning.

Texts.Chs: 你仁慈地把真菌虫带向了那么多的岛屿.
Texts.Eng: You have graciously transported blemmigans to this many islands.

Texts.Chs: 你已经经历过甜蜜而无梦的一夜. [这将会在你对抗梦魇时增强你的力量.]
Texts.Eng: You have known a sweet and dreamless sleep. [This will strengthen you when you struggle against Nightmares.]

Texts.Chs: 你已经了解了爱. 爱不会消散.
Texts.Eng: You have known love. It lingers.

Texts.Chs: 你在安忒外室游荡.
Texts.Eng: You have looked around Anthe's outermost chambers.

Texts.Chs: 你在珊瑚之源的象棋比赛中有了自己的记号.
Texts.Eng: You have made your mark in the chess-contests of the Principles of Coral.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见过了海冰之塔下那些蹲着的人.
Texts.Eng: You have met the squatters at the tower of zee ice.

Texts.Chs: 你有一名专业的, 甚至可能是有从业执照的医生的帮助.
Texts.Eng: You have professional, perhaps even qualified, medical assistance.

Texts.Chs: You have purchased Zubmariner!
Texts.Eng: You have purchased Zubmariner!

Texts.Chs: 你从残骸中找回了一箱骨雕. 那货物本来是要送去骨雕馆的.
Texts.Eng: You have recovered a box of bone carvings from a wreck. The cargo was intended for delivery to Scrimshander.

Texts.Chs: 你在骨雕馆放下了真菌虫.
Texts.Eng: You have released blemmigans into Scrimshander.

Texts.Chs: 你从偷灵魂的猴子的领地回来了.
Texts.Eng: You have returned from the land of soul-stealing monkeys.

Texts.Chs: 你见到了黎明机器之后的东西
Texts.Eng: You have seen behind the Dawn Machine

Texts.Chs: 你得到了啮齿类动物战争的第一手资料.
Texts.Eng: You have seen first-hand the Rodent War.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见过了海盗王的领地.
Texts.Eng: You have seen the Pirate-King's domain.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见到了产出做劳工的粘土人的城市.
Texts.Eng: You have seen the city where the Clay Men are made for labour.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见过了保管火焰的山岗.
Texts.Eng: You have seen the hill where the fire is kept.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见到了破碎船壳的家.
Texts.Eng: You have seen the home of sundered hulls.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见过了那里的冰和盐.
Texts.Eng: You have seen the ice and salt.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见到了只允许一张面孔存在的岛屿.
Texts.Eng: You have seen the isle where one face only is permitted.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见过了那里的灯光和悬崖.
Texts.Eng: You have seen the lights and the cliffs.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见到了那个视象棋为圣物的地方.
Texts.Eng: You have seen the place where chess is holy.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见到了这些半死的人会去的地方.
Texts.Eng: You have seen the place where the half-dead go.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见到了那个蘑菇看上去比表面多得多的地方.
Texts.Eng: You have seen the place where they have more mushrooms than sense.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见过了倒在海中的破碎城堡.
Texts.Eng: You have seen the shattered citadel that lies in the zee.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见到了那些人是如何服侍古井的.
Texts.Eng: You have seen where the Service of the Well is performed.
You have seen where the world ends. Behind those peaks of ice, something colder by far.

Texts.Chs: 你在救世主岩礁放下了真菌虫.他们会填满所有没被蜘蛛网堵住的黑暗缝隙.
Texts.Eng: You have sown blemmigans at Saviour's Rocks. They'll fill any dark crevice not blocked with cobweb.

Texts.Chs: 你在隐逸之地放下了真菌虫. 也许他们会和下面的巨兽做朋友.
Texts.Eng: You have sown blemmigans into Hideaway. Perhaps they'll befriend the beast.

Texts.Chs: 你在光之礼拜堂放下了真菌虫.他们不会很享受这些东西的.
Texts.Eng: You have sown the Chapel's island with blemmigans. They probably won't enjoy it much.

Texts.Chs: 你在可汗之心安插了间谍.
Texts.Eng: You have spies in Khan's Heart.

Texts.Chs: 你在玛瑙港安插了间谍.
Texts.Eng: You have spies in Port Carnelian.

Texts.Chs: 你被食人的欲望污染了.
Texts.Eng: You have the cannibal taint.

Texts.Chs: 你被告知了一项深深伤害到你的真相.
Texts.Eng: You have told a truth that cuts deep.

Texts.Chs: You have unlocked the Parabolan Panther mascot in Sunless Sea!
Texts.Eng: You have unlocked the Parabolan Panther mascot in Sunless Sea!

Texts.Chs: 你去过一所崇尚故事的房屋.
Texts.Eng: You have visited a house that worships stories.

Texts.Chs: You joined yourself to the ironbird, to carry winter to city after city
Texts.Eng: You joined yourself to the ironbird, to carry winter to city after city

Texts.Chs: 你现在知道了一点点他的过去.
Texts.Eng: You know a little more about his past, now.

Texts.Chs: 你了解了一点是什么驱使着她.
Texts.Eng: You know a little of what drives her.

Texts.Chs: 你知道关于地下海的一些事.
Texts.Eng: You know something of the Unterzee.

Texts.Chs: 你知道了去医院的路, 还有去警卫室和米希尔庙的.
Texts.Eng: You know your way to the Hospital, the Guard-House and Mihir's temple.

Texts.Chs: 你必须重振对抗尼达的七人团.
Texts.Eng: You must restore the Seven Against Nidah.

Texts.Chs: 你什么都不用解释. 在潜艇方面, 你就是专家.
Texts.Eng: You need nothing explained. On zubmarines, you are an expert.

Texts.Chs: 你需要找到其他地方居住.最好快一点.
Texts.Eng: You need to find somewhere better to live. And soon.

Texts.Chs: 你从来都没在羊岛找到过什么新闻,然而对于将军来说这也是情报.
Texts.Eng: You never find much news on Mutton Island, but it's intelligence for the Admiralty nevertheless.

Texts.Chs: 你在这里找她, 你在那里找她.
Texts.Eng: You seek her here, you seek her there.

Texts.Chs: 你从去悲伤蜘蛛躲藏地的旅途中活了下来.
Texts.Eng: You survived a trip to the lair of the sorrow-spiders.

Texts.Chs: 你穿过了一片白色的树林, 并带着某种想法归来.
Texts.Eng: You travelled through a white wood, and returned with a notion.

Texts.Chs: 你理解了言语的力量.
Texts.Eng: You understand the power of the spoken word.

Texts.Chs: You used the ironbird's energies to change Iria forever, breaking the power of the Circle of Bullets
Texts.Eng: You used the ironbird's energies to change Iria forever, breaking the power of the Circle of Bullets

Texts.Chs: You used the ironbird's energies to change Iria forever, breaking the power of the Ocular Guard
Texts.Eng: You used the ironbird's energies to change Iria forever, breaking the power of the Ocular Guard

Texts.Chs: You used the ironbird's energies to change Iria forever, breaking the power of the Scarf and Feather Society
Texts.Eng: You used the ironbird's energies to change Iria forever, breaking the power of the Scarf and Feather Society

Texts.Chs: 你是一名贮蜜者葬礼盛宴的荣誉宾客.
Texts.Eng: You were guest of honour at one of the funeral-feasts of the Replete.

Texts.Chs: 你将会来过这里.
Texts.Eng: You will have been there.

Texts.Chs: 你将从伊瑞暮归来.
Texts.Eng: You will return from Irem.

Texts.Chs: 你下次停泊时会找到些新的故事. [当你在海上航行足够的时间后会得到这个.]
Texts.Eng: You'll find a story when you next make port. [You'll receive this from time to time as you travel the zee.]

Texts.Chs: 你最终会移开视线. [如果你已经订立了遗嘱,你能把这个东西变成留给后继者的遗物.]
Texts.Eng: You'll look away, eventually. [If you've made an Ironclad Will, you can convert these into Heirlooms for your successor.]

Texts.Chs: 你可以在富含氧气的旮旯水中呼吸 - 暂时的.
Texts.Eng: You're able to breathe the oxygen-rich waters of Nook - for the time being.

Texts.Chs: 你被要求找到一名在达哈被囚禁的人.
Texts.Eng: You've been asked to find a certain person imprisoned in Dahut.

Texts.Chs: 你被要求收集一个包裹并返回伦敦.不要空手回来.
Texts.Eng: You've been asked to pick up a package and return it to London. Don't come back without it.

Texts.Chs: 你在猎户塔楼的三姐妹那里逗留过.
Texts.Eng: You've been known to visit the three sisters of Hunter's Keep.

Texts.Chs: 你选择加速.让我们看看他们能不能赶上这!
Texts.Eng: You've been pacing yourself. Let's see them keep up with this!

Texts.Chs: 你已经去过了可汗之心, 那里的电灯很亮,几大部族都在磨砺他们的利爪.
Texts.Eng: You've been to Khan's Heart, where the electric lights glow and the clans sharpen their claws.

Texts.Chs: 你去过了一个记忆之城, 并将自己的一部分抛在了身后.
Texts.Eng: You've been to the City of Remembrance and left something of yourself behind.

Texts.Chs: 你见到了真菌之母.
Texts.Eng: You've been to the Mother of Fungus.

Texts.Chs: 你已经去过了巨大大嘴.
Texts.Eng: You've been to the great Maw.

Texts.Chs: 你已经去过了海中巨兽走向死亡的地方.
Texts.Eng: You've been where the beasts of the zee go to die.

Texts.Chs: 你为死亡聚居地带来了些新的, 紫色的生命.
Texts.Eng: You've brought new, and purple, life to the tomb-colonies.

Texts.Chs: 你在阿斯蒂沃放下了真菌虫, 看起来真丢人.
Texts.Eng: You've dropped blemmigans on Aestival, which seems rather a shame.

Texts.Chs: 你发现了隐藏的志向! 殖民并开发阿斯蒂沃来建立你自己的王国.
Texts.Eng: You've found a hidden Ambition! Colonise and improve Aestival to found your own kingdom.

Texts.Chs: 你们日益熟络, 这安全吗?
Texts.Eng: You've grown closer. Is that safe?

Texts.Chs: 你听到了祭司的言语 - 看到了他红白相间的笑容.
Texts.Eng: You've heard the priest's words - seen his smile of red and white.

Texts.Chs: 你向手掌帝国介绍了真菌虫.
Texts.Eng: You've introduced blemmigans to the Empire of Hands.

Texts.Chs: 你交了个汗国的朋友.
Texts.Eng: You've made Khaganian friends.

Texts.Chs: 你和切洛内特的海兽猎人成为了朋友.
Texts.Eng: You've made friends among the beast-slayers of the Chelonate.

Texts.Chs: 你和坦途做了朋友.
Texts.Eng: You've made friends with Temtum.

Texts.Chs: 你见过了覆叶继承人的父亲.
Texts.Eng: You've met the father of the Cladery Heir.

Texts.Chs: 你将真菌虫放到了爪下.
Texts.Eng: You've released blemmigans into the Undercrow.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见过了遗失邮差们的岛屿.
Texts.Eng: You've seen the Island of Lost Postmen.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见到了古大陆的心流出的血液之河.
Texts.Eng: You've seen the blood that flows from the Continent's heart.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见过了巨龟的漂浮残骸.
Texts.Eng: You've seen the floating corpse of the Turtle.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见过了那些被黎明机器选中的人.
Texts.Eng: You've seen the house of the elect of the Dawn Machine.
You've seen the hungry place at the world's edge.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见到了深寻王王座附近的东西.
Texts.Eng: You've seen what grows around the Fathomking's throne.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见到了一个人挖掘秘密太深会发生什么.
Texts.Eng: You've seen what happens when one digs too deep for secrets.
You've seen where the Khanate rebels lair.

Texts.Chs: 你已经见到了海泽中那被光明洗礼过的地方.
Texts.Eng: You've seen where the sunlight brushes the zee.

Texts.Chs: 你有了些玩折鳃鳗的经历.
Texts.Eng: You've some experience playing Snaplamprey.

Texts.Chs: 你在亚当之路放下了真菌虫.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans at Adam's Way.

Texts.Chs: 你在安忒放下了真菌虫.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans at Anthe.

Texts.Chs: 你在达哈放下了真菌虫.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans at Dahut.

Texts.Chs: 你在德莫岛放下了真菌虫.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans at Demeaux Island.

Texts.Chs: 你在伊瑞暮放下了真菌虫. 或者, 也许, 你将会散播它们.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans at Irem. Or, perhaps, you will sow them.

Texts.Chs: 你在可汗之心放下了真菌虫.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans at Khan's Heart.

Texts.Chs: 你在可汗之影放下了真菌虫.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans at Khan's Shadow.

Texts.Chs: 你在玛瑙港放下了真菌虫.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans at Port Carnelian.

Texts.Chs: 你在切洛内特放下了真菌虫.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans at the Chelonate.

Texts.Chs: 你在猫岛放下了真菌虫. 这会对蜜蜂有什么影响?
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans at the Isle of Cats. How will they react to the bees?

Texts.Chs: 你在玫瑰之门放下了真菌虫. 希望他们不介意烟味.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans in Rosegate. Hopefully they don't mind smoke.

Texts.Chs: 你在船墟放下了真菌虫.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans in Wrack.

Texts.Chs: 你在修道院岩礁放了真菌虫. 毫无疑问如果修女们反对,她们会做出一些反应.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans on Abbey Rock. No doubt if the nuns object, they'll do something about it.

Texts.Chs: 你在加德的哀悼放下了真菌虫. 也许它们能在某处找到安身之地.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans on Gaider's Mourn. Perhaps they'll find a foothold somewhere.

Texts.Chs: 你在神落放下了真菌虫.毫无疑问它们能在破碎城堡的走廊里找到养分.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans on Godfall. No doubt they will find nutrients in the corridors of the Shattered Citadel.

Texts.Chs: 你在猎户塔楼放下了真菌虫.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans on Hunter's Keep.

Texts.Chs: 你在农西奥放下了真菌虫.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans on Nuncio.

Texts.Chs: 你在皮格莫特放下了真菌虫...也许是在微妙的平衡中引入了第三个势力.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans on Pigmote Isle... perhaps introducing a third term to a delicate equation.

Texts.Chs: 你在碎心国放下了真菌虫.谁知道会发生什么事情?
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans on Polythreme. Who knows what will come of it?

Texts.Chs: 你在维瑟吉放下了真菌虫. 它很难让这个地方变得更陌生.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans on Visage. It can hardly make the place any stranger.

Texts.Chs: 你在一艘灯塔船上放了真菌虫.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans on a Light-Ship.

Texts.Chs: 你在牧羊人岛放下了真菌虫. 没人会相信的.
Texts.Eng: You've sown blemmigans on the Shepherd Isles. No-one will believe it.

Texts.Chs: 你已经和宏伟晶洞的指挥官谈过. 但是你的记忆有点模糊.
Texts.Eng: You've spoken to the Commodore in Grand Geode. But your memory is a little hazy.
You've visited the Fortas Kettle.

Texts.Chs: 你让一名陌生人上了船.这可能意味着一些事情会发生.
Texts.Eng: You've welcomed a stranger aboard your ship. This may lead to complications.

Texts.Chs: 你的父亲
Texts.Eng: Your Father

Texts.Chs: 父亲的遗骨: 为深寻王带来的永恒之树的果实
Texts.Eng: Your Father's Bones: Fruit of the Eternal Tree for the Fathomking

Texts.Chs: 父亲的遗骨: 深寻王的钥匙
Texts.Eng: Your Father's Bones: The Fathomking's Key

Texts.Chs: 父亲的遗骨: 为深寻王准备的传奇之心
Texts.Eng: Your Father's Bones: a Legend's Heart for the Fathomking

Texts.Chs: 父亲的遗骨: 为深寻王准备的科学奇迹
Texts.Eng: Your Father's Bones: a Miracle of Science for the Fathomking

Texts.Chs: 父亲的遗骨: 为深寻王准备的天空之光
Texts.Eng: Your Father's Bones: a Sky-Light for the Fathomking

Texts.Chs: 父亲的遗骨: 为深寻王准备的一名自愿的宾客
Texts.Eng: Your Father's Bones: a Willing Guest for the Fathomking

Texts.Chs: 父亲的遗骨: 为深寻王准备的一个远古之物的结局
Texts.Eng: Your Father's Bones: an Eldest's End for the Fathomking

Texts.Chs: 你的赞助人建议你去卡米安运河.
Texts.Eng: Your Patron suggested the Cumaean Canal.

Texts.Chs: 你结识了朴素的助手.
Texts.Eng: Your acquaintance with the Austere Acolyte.

Texts.Chs: 你正在圣所之中.
Texts.Eng: Your current level in the Vault.

Texts.Chs: 你现在站在猴子的宫殿前.
Texts.Eng: Your current standing in the Monkey Court.

Texts.Chs: 你的财产正在增长.
Texts.Eng: Your estate grows.

Texts.Chs: 你送给雪豹部族的礼物给你带来了一点点好名声.
Texts.Eng: Your gifts to the Leopard Clan have assured you a little favour.

Texts.Chs: 你送给鲑鱼部族的礼物给你带来了一点点好名声.
Texts.Eng: Your gifts to the Taimen Clan have assured you a little favour.

Texts.Chs: 你的航行将会继续. [你建立了一个船长的朝代. 这将会在船长之间流传, 除非有些事情发生并终止了它.]
Texts.Eng: Your line will continue. [You have established a dynasty of zee-captains. This will persist between captains, unless something happens to end it.]

Texts.Chs: 你的肝脏将不受任何影响.
Texts.Eng: Your liver is impervious to any abuse.

Texts.Chs: 你的间谍网络需要你.
Texts.Eng: Your network needs you.

Texts.Chs: 你的猎物已经被征服, 但是这个剩了下来.
Texts.Eng: Your prey is vanquished, but this remains.

Texts.Chs: 你已远远超过你的对手.
Texts.Eng: Your rivals are a good way behind you.

Texts.Chs: 你的船正在享受气动传输带来的好处.
Texts.Eng: Your ship enjoys the benefits of pneumatic engineering.

Texts.Chs: 你船上的仪器依赖于夜晚的能量. 你也许使用了不明仪器.
Texts.Eng: Your ship's instrumentation relies on the energies of night. You may employ Unclear Devices.

Texts.Chs: 你的灵魂居住于手掌帝国
Texts.Eng: Your soul resides in the Empire of Hands

Texts.Chs: 你的人口正在提升.
Texts.Eng: Your subjects increase.

Texts.Chs: 你的故事迷住了听众.
Texts.Eng: Your tales have captivated listeners.

Texts.Chs: 你在海中度过的时间会改变你...还有伦敦.
Texts.Eng: Your time at zee will change you... and London.

Texts.Chs: 你的言语将会把它们沉入海中.
Texts.Eng: Your words will sink them into the zee.

Texts.Chs: 你为朴素的助手做的工作向你介绍了三号要塞里的其他人.
Texts.Eng: Your work for the Austere Acolyte has introduced you to others on the Island.

Texts.Chs: 海兽们能够击沉人们之前建造过的所有船只.末日级是为了打破这个惯例而建造的.
Texts.Eng: Zee-beasts can overwhelm any ship ever built. The Eschatologue was designed to be the exception.
